Class Geometric3

A multivector with a Euclidean metric and Cartesian coordinates.

reflect

  • reflect(n: VectorE3)
    • Defined in davinci-newton/math/Geometric3.ts:1260

    Sets this multivector to its reflection in the plane orthogonal to vector n.

    Mathematically,

    this ⟼ - n this n

    Geometrically,

    Reflects this multivector in the plane orthogonal to the unit vector, n.

    If n is not a unit vector then the result is scaled by n squared.

    Parameters

    • n: VectorE3

      The unit vector that defines the reflection plane.

rotorFromDirections

  • rotorFromDirections(a: VectorE3, b: VectorE3)
    • Defined in davinci-newton/math/Geometric3.ts:1384

    Computes a rotor, R, from two unit vectors, where R = (|b||a| + b a) / sqrt(2 |b||a|(|b||a| + b << a))

    The result is independent of the magnitudes of a and b.

    Parameters

    • a: VectorE3

      The starting vector

    • b: VectorE3

      The ending vector
